<section class="vossa-section problem" id="problem">
  <svg class="breath-pattern" viewBox="0 0 1200 200" preserveAspectRatio="none">
    <g fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1">
      <path d="M 0 80 Q 200 30, 400 80 T 800 80 T 1200 80"/>
      <path d="M 0 110 Q 200 60, 400 110 T 800 110 T 1200 110"/>
      <path d="M 0 140 Q 200 90, 400 140 T 800 140 T 1200 140"/>
    </g>
  </svg>
  <div class="vossa-section-inner center">
    <p class="vossa-eyebrow">{{ section.settings.eyebrow }}</p>
    <h2>{{ section.settings.heading }}</h2>
    <p class="vossa-sub">{{ section.settings.sub }}</p>

    <div class="vossa-problem-grid">
      <div class="vossa-problem-card glass-card">
        <div class="vossa-icon-bubble">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <p class="vossa-card-tag">Cardiovascular</p>
        <h3>Higher Blood Pressure</h3>
        <p>When the airway collapses repeatedly through the night, the body fires off stress signals that can push blood pressure higher over the long run. Open airways protect your heart.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vossa-problem-card glass-card">
        <div class="vossa-icon-bubble">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21 12.79A9 9 0 1 1 11.21 3 7 7 0 0 0 21 12.79z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <p class="vossa-card-tag">Sleep Quality</p>
        <h3>Snoring & Sleep Apnea</h3>
        <p>Mouth breathing narrows the airway, ramping up vibration and disrupting the deep, restorative stages of sleep. You wake up groggy because your brain never finished the job.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vossa-problem-card glass-card">
        <div class="vossa-icon-bubble">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 5.5A6.5 6.5 0 0 0 5.5 12c0 4 2.5 6 6.5 9.5 4-3.5 6.5-5.5 6.5-9.5A6.5 6.5 0 0 0 12 5.5z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <p class="vossa-card-tag">Oral Health</p>
        <h3>Dry Mouth & Gum Disease</h3>
        <p>Saliva is your mouth's first defence against bacteria. Mouth breathing dries it up — leaving teeth and gums vulnerable, and mouth-breathers show notably higher cavity risk.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Problem",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "eyebrow",
      "label": "Eyebrow",
      "default": "The Problem"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "<p>4 out of 5 people are airflow limited.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "sub",
      "label": "Sub-headline",
      "default": "Chronic mouth breathing isn't just an annoying habit. It quietly wrecks your sleep architecture, slows your recovery, and erodes your oral health \u2014 and most people never connect the dots."
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
